<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 08 at 9:09AM CDT  by NWS QuadCities</headline>
<description>...Heavy Rain Producing Showers and Thunderstorms...
At 905 AM CDT...Doppler radar indicated showers and thunderstorms
with heavy rain moving across the area. The storms are producing
torrential rainfall with around an inch of rain occurring in 30
minutes or less in some locations. This will likely result in
minor flooding of low lying or poorly drained areas, and lead to
ponding water on roadways. Some of the stronger storms may also
produce wind gusts up to 40 MPH.
If driving across the area this morning, please take it slow with
the wet roadways and reduced visibilities. Never drive into areas
where water covers the road!</description>
